Explanation of the Code Structure
Model Class (Student):

Contains attributes like name, id, and grade.
Provides getter and setter methods for these attributes.
View Class (StudentView):

Contains the displayStudentDetails(Student student) method.
This method prints the details of a Student object to the console.
Controller Class (StudentController):

Manages the communication between the Student model and the StudentView.
Provides methods to update the student's attributes and refresh the view with the updated details.
Test Class (main method):

Demonstrates the creation of a Student model, a StudentView, and a StudentController.
Shows how to use the controller to update the student's details and refresh the view to display those changes.
